      "message": "we should never put any ANDROID-specific code into the QEMU2 codebase. Instead, create a callback in QEMU and make the glue code set it to something that injects the changes you want to do.\nThis is the only way to keep QEMU code as close to upstream as we can (just a single setcallback + single callback call), while extending it as we need\nTake a look at the qemu_thread_register_setup_callback() in include/qemu/thread.h and its usage to inject our looper implementation into all QEMU threads",
